35-- | Implementation of relational operators.
36ropsCoxRange :: (D.CContent c) => [C.Rop c]
37ropsCoxRange = Op.ropList "cox-calc"
38    --        CONSTRUCTOR       USAGE                             ATTRIBUTE
39    [ Op.def  consRange         "range /N -from E -to E"          "-term . -from -to"
40    , Op.def  consRangeYear     "range-year /N -from /P to /P"    "-term . -from -to"
41    , Op.def  consRangeMonth    "range-month /N -from /P to /P"   "-term . -from -to"
42    , Op.def  consRangeDay      "range-day /N -from /P to /P"     "-term . -from -to"
43    , Op.def  consRangeHour     "range-hour /N -from /P to /P"    "-term . -from -to"
44    , Op.def  consRangeMinute   "range-minute /N -from /P to /P"  "-term . -from -to"
45    , Op.def  consRangeSecond   "range-second /N -from /P to /P"  "-term . -from -to"
46    ]

48
49-- ----------------------  range
50
51-- $range
52--
53--  Add term @\/n@ @0@, @\/n@ @1@, ..., and @\/n@ @9@.
54--  
55--    > range /n -from 0 -to 9
56
57type RangeAttr c = (S.TermName, D.CopSet c, D.Cox c, D.Cox c)
58
59getRangeAttr :: (D.CContent c) => C.Intmed c -> B.Ab (RangeAttr c)
60getRangeAttr med =
61  do term     <- Op.getTerm med "-term"
62     coxLow   <- Op.getCox  med "-from"
63     coxHigh  <- Op.getCox  med "-to"
64     let cops = C.globalCopset $ C.ropGlobal med
65     Right (term, cops, coxLow, coxHigh)
66
67consRange :: (D.CContent c) => C.RopCons c
68consRange med = Right . relmapRange med =<< getRangeAttr med
69
70relmapRange :: (D.CContent c) => C.Intmed c -> RangeAttr c -> C.Relmap c
71relmapRange med = C.relmapFlow med . relkitRange
72
73relkitRange :: (D.CContent c) => RangeAttr c -> C.RelkitFlow c
74relkitRange _ Nothing = Right C.relkitNothing
75relkitRange (n, cops, coxLow, coxHigh) (Just he1) = Right kit2 where
76    he2      = D.headCons n he1
77    kit2     = C.relkitJust he2 $ C.RelkitOneToAbMany False f2 []
78    f2 _ cs  = do decLow    <- D.getDec $ D.coxRunCox cops he1 cs coxLow
79                  decHigh   <- D.getDec $ D.coxRunCox cops he1 cs coxHigh
80
81                  let low    = D.decimalNum decLow
82                      high   = D.decimalNum decHigh
83                      decs   = map D.pInteger [low .. high]
84
85                  Right $ map (: cs) decs
86
87

112-- ----------------------  range-day
113
114consRangeDay :: (D.CContent c) => C.RopCons c
115consRangeDay med = Right . relmapRangeDay med =<< getRangeAttr med
116
117relmapRangeDay :: (D.CContent c) => C.Intmed c -> RangeAttr c -> C.Relmap c
118relmapRangeDay med = C.relmapFlow med . relkitRangeDay
119
120relkitRangeDay :: (D.CContent c) => RangeAttr c -> C.RelkitFlow c
121relkitRangeDay = relkitRangeBy D.timeRangeDay
122
123relkitRangeBy :: (D.CContent c) => B.RangeBy D.Time -> RangeAttr c -> C.RelkitFlow c
124relkitRangeBy _ _ Nothing = Right C.relkitNothing
125relkitRangeBy range (n, cops, from, to) (Just he1) = Right kit2 where
126    he2      = D.headCons n he1
127    kit2     = C.relkitJust he2 $ C.RelkitOneToAbMany False f2 []
128    f2 _ cs  = do timeFrom  <-  D.getTime $ D.coxRunCox cops he1 cs from
129                  timeTo    <-  D.getTime $ D.coxRunCox cops he1 cs to
130                  let ts    =   map D.pTime $ range timeFrom timeTo
131                  Right $ map (: cs) ts

158-- ----------------------  range-second
159
160consRangeSecond :: (D.CContent c) => C.RopCons c
161consRangeSecond med = Right . relmapRangeSecond med =<< getRangeAttr med
162
163relmapRangeSecond :: (D.CContent c) => C.Intmed c -> RangeAttr c -> C.Relmap c
164relmapRangeSecond med = C.relmapFlow med . relkitRangeSecond
165
166relkitRangeSecond :: (D.CContent c) => RangeAttr c -> C.RelkitFlow c
167relkitRangeSecond = relkitRangeClock 1
168
169relkitRangeClock :: (D.CContent c) => Int -> RangeAttr c -> C.RelkitFlow c
170relkitRangeClock _ _ Nothing = Right C.relkitNothing
171relkitRangeClock sec (n, cops, from, to) (Just he1) = Right kit2 where
172    he2      = D.headCons n he1
173    kit2     = C.relkitJust he2 $ C.RelkitOneToAbMany False f2 []
174    f2 _ cs  = do clockFrom  <- D.getClock $ D.coxRunCox cops he1 cs from
175                  clockTo    <- D.getClock $ D.coxRunCox cops he1 cs to
176                  let range   = D.clockRangeBy $ D.clockStep sec
177                      clocks  = map D.pClock $ range clockFrom clockTo
178                  Right $ map (: cs) clocks
